abstract: Domino's Pizza reports fourth-quarter net income of $48 million, or 85 cents a share, up 7 percent from year-earlier period; results fall short of analyst expectations.
lead_paragraph: Higher costs took some of the shine off better-than-expected sales at established restaurants.

headline.main: Profit at Domino’s Pizza Falls Short of Forecast
